<TITLE> BCB Academy face uphill task </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)  Hosts GP-BCB Academy face an uphill task against Sri Lankan Development squad to save the match on the fourth and final day of the second four-day game in Chittagong. The hosts were 62-1, trailing by 375 runs in the second innings at the close of the third day on Tuesday after the Sri Lankan Development squad set a daunting 436-run target at the Bir Shreshtha Shaheed Ruhul Amin Stadium. Nasiruddin Faruque (33) along with Sagir Hossain (1) will open the innings of the final day with looking to avoid a successive second defeat. Resuming the day on 118-6, the hosts were wrapped up for 164 in reply to the visitors' first innings total of 423 all out. But the visitors enforce the follow-on. Overnight batsman Arafat Salahuddin (18) remained not out at 45 with three fours and three sixes. Sri Lanka declared their second innings at 178-9, taking an overall lead of 435 and then reduced the hosts to 62-1 at the close of Day 3. bd
